  "title": "Fighting camera manager",
  "description": "The Fighting Camera Manager is a component for a pawn camera that follows characters with a lot of settings.",
  "longDescription": "<p><a href=\"https://youtu.be/X6kKEpxtoRo\" rel=\"nofollow\">Preview Video</a></p><p><a href=\"https://youtu.be/GjpU_F_YC3c\" rel=\"nofollow\">Network support video</a></p><p><a href=\"https://discord.gg/p8NbUxPBxM\" rel=\"nofollow\">Discord support</a></p><p>The product has:</p><ul><li><strong>2D (2.5D) mode</strong> - This mode has a setting when players move in one line to the left or right</li><li><strong>3D mode</strong> - In this mode, players can move around the level freely.</li><li><strong>Zoom Min</strong> - How close is the camera to player</li><li><strong>Zoom Max</strong> - How far is the camera from player</li><li><strong>Auto zoom</strong> - The camera work</li><li><strong>Height offset</strong> - The camera works in the set parameters between Zoom Min and Max</li><li><strong>Offset Angle Yaw</strong> - Angle to rotate the camera closer to the player</li><li><strong>Angle pitch</strong> - Angle between view from below or view from above</li><li><strong>Smooth camera rotation</strong> - How sensitive the camera is to player movements</li><li><strong>Max Distance P2P</strong> - Maximum distance between players</li><li><strong>Offset side distance</strong> - Distance between the player and the edge of the screen</li><li>Two dispatchers to block the movement of players off the screen in the given parameters</li></ul><p><br /></p><p>The product is great for those who want to make a fighting game. It has lots settings and is easy to integrate.</p><p>It also has full network support and Local Multiplayer on 1 keyboard or gamepad</p>",
